text.tspan: 13.10ANNEX 10 INTAKE CRITERIA OF MALAYSIAN TRAINEES FOR EXECUTIVE OFFSHORE1) Minimum age - 18 years and not more than 25 years.2) SPM result with minimum ‘C’ or with strong credits in Bahasa Malaysia, English, Mathematics, Additional Mathematics andPhysics.3) Should have completed a Govt. Approved Diploma in Nautical Studies/ Govt. Approved Pre Sea Training Course.4) Cleared in 1st attempt.5) Eyesight: 6/6 vision in both eyes (without visual aids), no colour-blindness.6) Mentally and physically fit for sea – fitness certificate issued by Govt. approved doctor.7) Minimum height of 158cm and weight of 48kg (BMI: 18.5-24.9).8) Should be unmarried.9) Should clear the selection process of Executive Offshore (Interview + 16 PF psychometric Test).1) Minimum age - 18 years and not more than 25 years.2) SPM result with minimum ‘C’ or with strong credits in Bahasa Malaysia, English, Mathematics, Additional Mathematics andPhysics.3) Should have completed a Govt. Approved Diploma in Marine Engineering.4) Cleared in 1st attempt.5) Corrective lenses permitted, maximum power allowed is 200 for the above and no colour-blindness.6) Mentally and physically fit for sea – fitness certificate issued by Govt. approved doctor.7) Minimum height of 158cm and weight of 48kg (BMI: 18.5-24.9).8) Should be unmarried.9) Should clear the selection process of Executive Offshore (Interview + 16 PF psychometric Test).
